722729f-a.text:
Riverside Drive, east side, from 89th to 90th Streets. This is the old Bishop Potter Residence, which has been demolished, and a large
apartment house now occupies the site.
About 1925.
Brown Brothers.

722903f-a.text:
Riverside Park, at the foot of West 93rd Street, showing the Columbia Yacht Club, viewed from the Drive. In the foreground are the New York Central Railroad tracks which will disappear from view after completion of
the West Side Improvement Project.
Note the U. S. Naval ships silhouetted against the Palisades on the Jersey shore. No. 2 is the same site during the aforementioned construction period.
View 1: June 17, 1936
View 2: June 28, 1935
P. L. Sperr
